<F P=100> UNITED KINGDOM </F>
<H3> <TI>   Major Meets Jordanian Crown Prince </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1101215794 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1101215794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Royal Highness Crown Prince Hasan met British 
Prime Minister John Major in London tonight for discussion on 
the Middle East and bilateral ties. The meeting at 10 Downing 
Street centered on the political climate in the Middle East and 
the need for the respect of international law. 
  His Royal Highness related the situation in the region to 
human needs and development within the framework of sovereignty 
of all states in the area. Prince Hasan and Prime Minister 
Major also discussed ideas for regional and intraregional 
economic and trade cooperation, particularly with Europe, once a 
just and comprehensive peace is established in the region. The 
meeting, which followed Mr. Major's return from the NATO summit, 
also discussed the situation in the Balkans and UN efforts to 
end the conflict as well as Jordan's contribution to 
peacekeeping and its keenness to put an end to the bloodshed 
there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

