<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former SED Official Denies Paying Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1101142194 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 1200 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1101142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Werner] Girke, the former administrator of the 
foreign assets of the Socialist Unity Party of Germany [SED], 
has denied having forwarded funds to Russian nationalist 
Zhirinovskiy. In an interview with STERN, Girke stated that he 
met incidentally with Zhirinovskiy in Austria shortly before 
Christmas. He also rejected the accusation concerning embezzled 
SED assets. In fact, he said, over 53 million German marks [DM] 
have been transferred to accounts held on trust. Another DM6 
million will follow shortly. 

</TEXT>

