<H3> <TI>   Sends PDS Second Letter Threat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1001144194 Berlin NEUES DEUTSCHLAND in German 8-9 Jan 94 p 
4 </F>

<F P=103> AU1001144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin NEUES DEUTSCHLAND </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "ND-Funke": "`WAW' Repeated Murder Threats"] </F>
  [Text] Berlin -- The Berlin-Weissensee Party of Democratic 
Socialism [PDS] has again received a threatening letter from the 
neo-fascist "Weissensee Aryan Resistance" ("WAW"), after it had 
found a similar pamphlet in its mailbox on Monday. The letter 
from Friday [7 January] claims that the previous letter did not 
contain a murder threat against [former PDS Chairman Gregor] 
Gysi but "only" against all those who move about freely in the 
PDS office. The Office for the Protection of the Constitution is 
greeted with the remark that it will not catch the "WAW," 
instead, "we will catch you all." Just as in the first letter, 
an ultimatum is posed to the PDS for clearing out the office by 
the end of January. In flowery words the authors glorify Hitler 
and are outraged about being called fascists -- they are, on the 
contrary, National Socialists. The PDS office has filed another 
complaint with the police, who reportedly are watching the house 
more intensively now. According to findings by the Federal 
Office for the Protection of the Constitution, the "WAW" is a 
group of extremely militant neo-Nazis. 

</TEXT>

