<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Balladur: Economy `Hit Bottom' at End of 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1101201894 Paris AFP in English 1950 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1101201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, Jan 11 (AFP) -- French Prime Minister 
[Edouard Balladur] said Tuesday [11 January] that the French 
economy "hit bottom in the last part" of last year, and that 
France must "do everything possible to slow the rise in 
unemployment." 
  Speaking on the TF1 television channel, he also said that 
his 
government would see to it that there would be "no additional 
tax burden on the French people's income" in 1994. 
  The French economy was in recession for most of last year, 
and the unemployment rate now stands at 12 percent. It is 
universally expected to rise further in the coming months. 
  He had previously expressed the opinion that the economy has 
now come out of recession. 

</TEXT>

