<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Cypriot Coalition Receives Vote of Confidence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1201100994 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1000 GMT 12 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1201100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Party-Republican Turkish Party 
coalition government has received a vote of confidence. 
  Of the 48 deputies who participated in the vote this 
morning, 
28 voted in favor of the government and 20 against. Two 
deputies did not participate in the Assembly session because 
they are on leave. 
  In a speech after the vote, Prime Minister Hakki Atun said 
that the aim of his government is to run a parliamentarian and 
democratic system through the Assembly in the most effective and 
fruitful way. Our aim is to run the state in the best possible 
way, he added, to strengthen it, and to make our people 
prosperous and happy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

