<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Envoy Supports UN Based Solution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101181094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1101181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia has affirmed that it supports a Cyprus 
solution based on the UN resolutions and criticized Turkey for 
repeatedly ignoring UN resolutions calling for the immediate 
withdrawal of the occupation troops. The Russian position was 
outlined today by Ambassador in Nicosia Boris Zenkov in his 
address at a meeting of the Larnaca district Rotary Club. 
  Russia will never support the establishment of two states in 
Cyprus, Mr. Zenkov stressed, and added that Cyprus is too small 
to be partitioned. He expressed the hope that there will be 
some positive developments this year for a balanced basis for 
negotiations in accordance with the Butrus-Ghali ideas and the 
confidence-building measures, which, as he put it, should be 
considered as a warm-up for a settlement. 
  Mr. Zenkov further noted that realism should be demonstrated 
about a Cyprus solution in the near future, adding that he does 
not believe the confidence-building measures will be implemented 
easily. He said: Many years will be necessary because of the 
long separation of the two communities. Mr. Zenkov also noted 
that he had recently informed President Glavkos Kliridhis and 
Mr. Rauf Denktas that if a solution is found to the Cyprus 
problem, Russia will propose that they be awarded the Nobel 
Peace Prize. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

