<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Troop Pullout From Somalia To Begin Early Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201111194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1012 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The withdrawal of the German UN 
contingent in Somalia will begin in early February via a 
combined land, air, and sea transport operation, German Defense 
Minister Volker Ruehe told the Bundestag Defense Committee in 
Bonn today. Personnel as well as sensitive equipment unsuitable 
for maritime shipment will be transported back to Germany by 
air. Seven ships are envisaged to bring back the bulk of the 
materiel. 
  During the withdrawal, the troops will make use of a 
stopover 
point halfway between Mogadishu and the German base at 
Beledweyne, as well as organize air and sea transshipment in the 
Somali capital. The last ship is due to leave Mogadishu on 19 
March. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

