<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Italy's Ciampi, Andreatta Support Use of Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101140794 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1200 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] NATO is ready to use force to break the sieges 
in Sarajevo, Tuzla, and Srebrenica. From Brussels, where the 
meeting of NATO memebers broke up a short time ago, a fresh 
warning was launched to the factions fighting in Bosnia. This 
time it seems that the alliance is serious in its intention. 
Francesco Mattioli reports from Brussels. [passage omitted] 
  [Mattioli] The Italians present at the meeting, [Prime 
Minister] Ciampi and [Foreign Minister] Andreatta are in 
agreement with the other countries. 
  [Begin Ciampi recording] I believe that the decisions made 
by 
the United Nations already leave open the possibility of air 
strikes. [end recording] 
  [Begin Andreatta recording] It is unimaginable that the 
secretary of the United Nations would not authorize actions in 
defense of the troops. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

