<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Socialist Euro-MPs Demand Right of GATT Approval </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201144694 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 1435 GMT 12 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201144694 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Geoff Meade, PRESS ASSOCIATION in Brussels] </F>
  [Text] The GATT deal on world trade, which took seven years 
of tough negotiating to secure, faces one more hurdle, it 
emerged today. Socialists in the European Parliament are now 
demanding the right of formal approval before the deal, with the 
promise of a multi-billion pound boost for the global economy, 
can be signed. 
  The 198-strong group of socialist Euro MPs, the biggest 
political bloc in the Strasbourg parliament, decided at talks 
today to use the GATT accord to flex their muscles as part of a 
long-running bid to exercise power. 
  The move holds no serious threat of upsetting the agreement 
but it could be delayed while Euro MPs challenge the formalities 
in the European Court of Justice, if necessary. 

</TEXT>

