<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranians Call Talks `Fruitful' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301092794 Tehran IRNA in English 0745 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301092794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, Jan 13, IRNA -- A senior Iranian 
parliamentarian here Wednesday [12 January] termed as fruitful 
his visit to Germany and talks with German officials. 
  Especial envoy of the Majles presiding board and head of 
Iran- Germany parliamentary friendship group Mohammad Javad 
Larijani told IRNA here that the Iranian parliamentary 
delegation visits Germany at the invitation of German parliament. 
  He said his visit aimed at clarifying Iran's stands on 
important regional issues, removing obstacles on mutual ties and 
identifying new grounds for future cooperation in the region. 
  Larijani added that the Iranian delegation and German 
authorities exchanged views on such topics as Central Asia, 
Iran-Germany cooperation in the region, Middle East issues and 
Israel-PLO deal. 
  The Iranian official further noted that the apostate Salman 
Rushdie's blasphemous book had harmed peace, security and 
understanding among followers of different religions because of 
insulting millions of Muslims. 
  He remarked that Iran's delayed debts to Germany was not 
considerable compared to the amount of Germany's exports to Iran 
during the past years and believed German Government could find 
reasonable settlements to the issue. 
  Larijani and his accompying delegation arrived here last 
Monday and will visit other German cities and hold talks with 
local officials. 

</TEXT>

