  [Text] Rome, Jan 13 (AFP) -- Italian Prime Minister Carlo 
Azeglio Ciampi offered his resignation Thursday [13 January] to 
President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro, a government official said. 
  However, Scalfaro was expected to ask Ciampi to stay in 
office pending early general elections. 

</TEXT>

