<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Giugni: Economy Has `Structural' Disadvantages </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201191094 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1521 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Italy lacks at least three million jobs. This is a 
"structural" disadvantage compared to other European countries 
which, together with a low level of education, makes the Italian 
situation especially difficult. This was said by Labor Minister 
Giugni at the presentation of a study of medium-term prospects 
for the labor market. 
  Giugni said that in October employment fell by 550,000 units 
compared with October 1992 and numbers unemployed increased by 
350,000 units, while the unemployment rate went up from 9.7 
percent to 11.3 percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-58430 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu009_k_94002" </HT>


