<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Solana Criticizes Bosnian Factions, Comments on Algeria </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201191594 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1400 GMT 12 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In statements to this station, Spanish Foreign 
Minister Javier Solana has repeated his criticisms of the 
leaders of the three warring factions in Bosnia who are making 
the work of the UN blue helmets difficult. 
  Javier Solana said it is frustrating and a scandal to see 
how 
these political and military leaders disregard their own 
citizens by hindering the arrival of aid the citizens need to 
survive the severe winter. 
  The minister also referred to the visit his Algerian 
counterpart, Mohamed Salah Dembri, is making to Spain. Algeria, 
said Javier Solana, is a country going through severe political 
and economic problems, as well as suffering from terrorist 
violence. Algeria has a great potential; however, it needs help 
to develop. Solana added that risks to Spanish companies and 
citizens in Algeria have to be minimized. 

</TEXT>

