<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bomb Explodes at Mexican Consulate in Bilbao </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1201154094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1417 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1201154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bilbao (Spain), 12 Jan (EFE) -- According to 
government sources, a bomb blast rocked the Mexican Consulate in 
Bilbao (northern Spain) without causing any great damage. 
  Government sources in Vizcaya Province reported that 
approximately 10 minutes before the explosion, an anonymous 
caller told police that a bomb was going to explode in the 
building where the consulate is located. No one was inside the 
consulate at the time of the blast. 
  Spanish police have sent explosives experts to the site to 
conduct an investigation. 
  Demonstrations have been organized in several parts of Spain 
in recent days to protest the Mexican Army's repression in the 
insurrection in Chiapas State, where peasants and Indians are 
demanding "land and freedom." 

</TEXT>

