<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Transport Discussed With Russian Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1201154194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1510 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1201154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Jan 12 (AA) -- A Russian technical 
delegation, currently in Turkey and Turkish Petroleum Company 
BOTAS officials on Wednesday [12 January] discussed the route of 
the petroleum coming from Russia, Caucasia and Central Asia. 
  BOTAS General Director Hayrettin Uzun answering AA 
reporter's 
questions on the visit said a Turkish-Russian joint study-group 
was decided to be set up to specify the cooperation fields on 
energy field during Premier Tansu Ciller's visit to Moscow in 
September. 
  Uzun said the joint study group holds talks on eight 
possible 
routes adding they mainly focus on a route which comes from 
Russia to Caucasia than to Georgia or Armenia. 
  Answering another question Uzun said a bargain with Russia 
for the price of an additional supply of two billion cubic 
meters of natural gas was out of question. 

</TEXT>

