<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ciampi: Scalfaro Must Decide on Parliament Dissolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201151694 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1430 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The debate on the motion of no confidence in the 
government proposed by [Radical leader Marco] Pannella has begun 
with a speech by Prime Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi. 
  Ciampi said it was not up to government to decide whether to 
dissolve parliament, and invited President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro, 
whom he will consult after the debate, to express his opinion 
about the situation, making it clear that he would place his 
mandate at Scalfaro's disposal. Ciampi pointed out the 
different positions of the political forces concerning the 
legislature's prospects: according to some they have been 
exhausted, while others say that important and specific acts 
still have to be carried out. 

</TEXT>

