<H3> <TI>   Greek Cypriots Reportedly Fire Across Border Zone </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1301204394 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 2030 GMT 13 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1301204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This evening, the Greek Cypriots added another 
border violation to those they have been carrying out for some 
time. TAK [Turkish Cypriot News Agency] reports that 10 shots 
were fired from two different places in the Greek Cypriot 
sector, some 150 meters into the border near the Lokmaci 
barricades in Lefkosa [Nicosia]. This provocative act occurred 
at around 1930. The Turkish Cypriot side did not respond in 
kind, so there were no casualties or damage to property. The 
Turkish Cypriot authorities have protested the incident to 
UNFICYP [UN Forces in Cyprus]. 

</TEXT>

