<H3> <TI>   Pakistani Minister Arrives for Economic Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1301151994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1301151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Shahid Khan, Pakistani state minister for the 
economy, has arrived on an official visit to Ankara. He was 
received at Ankara's Esenboga Airport by State Minister Nafiz 
Kurt. 
  In a statement at the airport, Kurt said that talks in 
Ankara 
will primarily focus on problems concerning a highway tender, 
which was taken on by a Turkish firm and later canceled by the 
Pakistani Government. Khan remarked in turn that bilateral 
economic relations as well as the problems in connection with 
the tender will be reviewed during his visit. Khan announced 
that he will convey invitations from the Pakistani prime 
minister and president to President Suleyman Demirel and Prime 
Minister Tansu Ciller. 

</TEXT>

