<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO To Study Plans To Bomb Serbian Positions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1601153394 Paris AFP in English 1218 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1601153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Brussels, Jan 16 (AFP) -- Urgent plans to bomb 
Serbian positions around the besieged Bosnian towns of 
Srebrenica and Tuzla will be studied by the North Atlantic 
Treaty Organisation here this week, a NATO source said at the 
weekend. 
  The plans, drawn up by UN commanders in Bosnia at the 
request 
of a NATO summit here last week, are due to be presented to UN 
Secretary-General Butrus Butrus-Ghali in Geneva on Monday [17 
January], then sent to NATO headquarters here. [passage omitted] 
  They ordered UN field commanders in Bosnia urgently to draw 
up plans for such strikes, which can be launched only if 
commanders on the scene ask for them and if Butrus-Ghali agrees. 
  NATO military planners will review the plans here this week, 
and ambassadors from the alliance's 16 member nations are 
scheduled to discuss them on Wednesday, the NATO source said. 
[passage omitted] 
  The NATO source added: "We clearly need a process where the 
political will (to bomb) is built up in NATO. The credibility 
of the West and the international community is at stake. I hope 
governments recognise the stakes." [passage omitted] 
  The NATO source said: "The question is just how does the UN 
see air power -- just to protect UN troops or as a political 
weapon?" [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

