<H3> <TI>   UN Spokeswoman Denies General Cot To Be Replaced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1701195094 Paris AFP in English 1930 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1701195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Geneva, Jan 17 (AFP) -- A UN spokeswoman here 
denied Monday [17 that the commander of UN forces in former 
Yugoslavia, French General Jean Cot, is to be replaced. 
  A United Nations official in New York, who declined to be 
identified, had said earlier that Cot, in command of the UN 
Protection Force (UNPROFOR) since July 1, "will soon leave his 
position." But Therese Gastaut, spokeswoman here for UN 
Secretary-General Butrus Butrus-Ghali, retorted: "That is not 
correct." 
  Asked straight out whether the secretary-general had 
dismissed Cot, she replied: "No." [passage omitted] 

