<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNHCR Urges West To Accept Refugees From Kosovo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401095594 Paris AFP in English 0246 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1401095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, Jan 14 (AFP) -- The UN High Commissioner 
for Refugees has called on European governments to accept 
asylum-seekers from Kosovo because of harsh winter conditions in 
the majority-Albanian Serbian province. 
  UNHCR spokeswoman Christiane Berthiaume said Thursday [13 
January] that some areas in Kosovo were without heat or 
electricity and that the human rights situation was also causing 
concern. 
  The organisation has asked governments not to send 
ayslum-seekers back at least until spring -- even if they do not 
fulfil the conditions for refugee status. 
  Switzerland gave temporary shelter to about 1,800 Albanians 
from Kosovo in 1993, but only accorded 100 of them refugee 
status. 
  Several political and religious groups recently tried to 
intervene with Bern authorities in a bid to prevent the 
expulsion of Kosovo Albanians. 

</TEXT>

