<H3> <TI>   SPOe Receives Death Threat Against Mayor Zilk </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1501195394 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 15 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1501195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Death Threat Against Mayor Zilk"] </F>
  [Text] A death threat against Vienna Mayor Helmut Zilk, 
who is still in the hospital after a letter-bomb attack, was 
received at the headquarters of the Social Democratic Party of 
Austria [SPOe] on Friday [14 January]. An anonymous caller 
threatened that Zilk will suffer the same fate as city 
councillor Heinz Nittel, who was shot dead on 1 May 1981. Party 
secretary Grete Dumser stated that the caller told the central 
office of the SPOe that he wanted to "make a political 
statement." He was then connected with the party's service 
office where he voiced his threat. The state police have 
initiated investigations. 

</TEXT>

