<H3> <TI>   Attackers of U.S. Athlete Sentenced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1801121594 Munich ARD Television Network in German 2145 
GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1801121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich ARD Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The two main participants in the skinhead attack 
against U.S. tobogganists in the Thuringian city of Oberhof have 
been sentenced to youth custody of two years and eight months 
and one year, respectively. The municipal court in Suhl found 
them guilty of grievous bodily harm. In October, along with 
other skinheads, the two men beat up U.S. tobogganist Duncan 
Kennedy, who tried to protect a black teammate. The defendants 
apologized to their victim today. Former offenses of the two 
men were included in the verdict. 

</TEXT>

