<H3> <TI>   Government `Assumes' Russian Reforms will Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701151794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1441 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1701151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- According to government spokesman 
Dieter Vogel, the German Government has "taken careful note" of 
the events in Moscow surrounding the resignation of Yegor 
Gaydar, the first deputy chairman of the Council of Ministers. 
Vogel told journalists in Bonn today that the Federal 
Government assumes that the policy of reform will be continued 
in Russia. The German Government does not have the slightest 
grounds for doubting this. It also wanted the policy of reform 
to be continued, Vogel is quoted as saying. 

