<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Patrol Attacks Greek Fishing Boat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701193094 Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 17 Jan 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> NC1701193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At 1600 yesterday a Turkish patrol boat attacked the 
Greek fishing boat "Ayios Yeoryios" six miles off Samos. The 
Turks pursued and fired shots to immobilize the boat just two 
and a half miles from the island's shore. They later tried to 
tow it to Turkey, but were unsuccessful because the Greek 
freighter "Avandi," which sailed from Karlovasi Harbor, arrived 
carrying port authority officials and soldiers. 
  The Turks were frightened, and abandoned their efforts. 
Brothers Panayiotis and Mikhail Dhritsakis, each married with 
three children, were aboard the fishing boat and in shock from 
the attack. The Samos Port police boats pursued the Turks to 
international waters. 

</TEXT>

