<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Urges Iran To Pardon German Citizen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401170494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1544 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Germany's Foreign Minister Klaus 
Kinkel has urgently appealed to Iran to pardon the German Helmut 
Szimkus, sentenced to death for espionage. The German 
Government regards the death sentence recently confirmed by 
Iran's supreme court as an "extremely serious affair," Kinkel 
said in Bonn today during talks with Mohamad Larijani, secretary 
of the International Relations Committee of Iran's Supreme 
Council for National Security. Kinkel welcomed the intention 
voiced by Larijani to press for a resolution of the case, the 
Foreign Ministry added. 

</TEXT>

