<H3> <TI>   Right-Wing `Extremist' Party Plans Congress </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401145994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1328 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Frankfurt/Main (DDP/ADN) -- An extraordinary 
party congress of the right-wing extremist National Democratic 
Party of Germany [Nationaldemokratische Partei Deutschlands] 
(NPD) apparently is to be held in the town of Ehringshausen (in 
Lahn-Dill rural district) in Hesse. This emerges from a letter 
in DDP/ADN's possession from the NPD party executive to party 
members dated 10 January. According to the letter, the congress 
is to begin at 1000 in the Volkshalle in Ehringshausen. 
  The Lahn-Dill branch of the DGB [German Trade Union 
Federation] has already announced a counterdemonstration and 
rally, permits for which have already been applied for and 
approved, according to a spokesman. The counterdemonstrators 
intend to gather at 0900 at Ehringshausen station. 
  The police in Giessen also expect the party congress to go 
ahead in Ehringhausen, but do not rule out that the meeting may 
be held elsewhere. The NPD had named various places in 
Thuringia and Hesse during the run-up to the congress, 
apparently in order to confuse the counterdemonstrators. 
Giessen police said they would be responding flexibly. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

