<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Demirel Warns Greece To Share Aegean </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1401210794 Istanbul TURKIYE in Turkish 14 Jan 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> NC1401210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul TURKIYE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara -- In his assessment of Greek oil prospecting 
around Thasos Island, President Suleyman Demirel warned: 
"Problems will arise if Greece acts like `this is my sea, my 
lake' with regard to the Aegean." 
  Indicating that for Greece to try to do something in a sea 
in 
which Turkey has interests would lead to problems, President 
Demirel said: "When I say these things, they immediately get 
offended. I am not the one creating tension. I merely want all 
the problems to be resolved peacefully." 
  Indicating that Greece has nothing to be gained in the 
present situation by fomenting and escalating a crisis with 
Turkey, the president said: "You are not always at fault in a 
traffic accident. You might be a very good driver, but someone 
might come along and collide with you." 
  When reminded that he brought Prime Minister Ciller into 
politics, Demirel said he cannot comment on the prime minister's 
statements and views and added: "Whether I defend or criticize 
them, it will still open the way to various speculations. I am 
not an inspector of the prime minister; I too am a mere voting 
citizen." 

</TEXT>

