<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Launches Air, Ground Operations in Agri Area </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1401181394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1401181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Gursel Balci video report from Agri Mountain region] </F>
  [Text] In operations launched five days ago, war planes 
bombed terrorist targets in the northern section of Agri 
Mountain. Yesterday, security forces engaged a group of 150 
terrorists in a clash in the Korugan-(?Kislagi) region. The 
area harboring the terrorists was encircled by two battalions 
and subjected to intense artillery and mortar fire. Cobra 
helicopters were also used. The terrorists, who sustained heavy 
casualties, are taking advantage of the 2-meter high snow and 
mountainous terrain and carrying their dead and wounded to 
Kupgolu area. 
  Today, security forces began their search operations in the 
area of the fighting. During the operations, acting on 
information that a group of terrorists descended from Agri 
Mountain into the surrounding villages, security forces searched 
the villages located between the mountain and Armenia. A total 
of 68 persons -- eight organization members, 28 abettors, and 32 
wanted suspects -- were captured during the searches. With 
these people, security forces seized three Kalashnikov rifles 
and large quantities of unlicensed weapons and rounds of 
ammunition. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

