<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agri Operations Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1601192794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1601192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Gursel Balci video report from Agri Mountain region] </F>
  [Text] The operations launched on Agri Mountain are 
continuing despite the heavy fog and snow fall. Sikorsky and 
Cobra helicopters are participating in the operations when the 
weather permits. The bodies of 28 terrorists were found during 
searches conducted following the clashes between the security 
forces and the terrorists in the Korugan-Kislagi region on 
Thursday [13 January]. 
  Furthermore, it has been determined that at least 20 of the 
some 100 terrorists who were under fire yesterday night have 
been killed, and many have been injured. Based on the blood and 
other evidence, it has also been determined that many injured 
were taken to other regions of the mountain. 
  A terrorist shelter was discovered during an intense 
operation in the northern peaks of Agri Mountain. Various 
equipment, a generator, a television, a video machine, a camera, 
lighting and medical equipment, and tonnes of foodstuffs were 
found in the shelter, which has two separate entrances. It was, 
however, impossible to film due to the heavy fog around the 
mountain. Operations are continuing in the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

