solidarity documents were signed adding that these two countries 
have similar views on problems. 
  He said a Black Sea Economic Cooperation (BSEC) meeting will 
be held in Tbilisi at the beginning of summer adding that a 
summit will be held between heads of states and governments in 
case the other BSEC member countries accept it. 
  Chikvaidze thanked for Turkish Foreign Ministry's 
preparations for Shevardnadze's visit adding that Turkey and 
Georgia completed infrastructure of the bilateral relations in 
political, economical and cultural fields. 

