<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report on Greek Commandos Creates Interest, Criticism </TI></H3>
<H4>   Turkish Cypriots Seek Information </H4>
<F P=102> TA1501073894 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 2030 GMT 14 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1501073894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Defense has made 
representations to UNFICYP [UN Force in Cyprus] in connection 
with the Greek commandos that have gone to South Cyprus. 
  TAK [Turkish Cypriot News Agency] reports that the Ministry 
asked the UNFICYP for information about the Greek commandos. 
  According to information published in the Greek Cypriot 
press, a planeload of Greek commandos secretly arrived in South 
Cyprus yesterday. Greek Cypriot sources assessed the situation 
as a delivery of troops within the framework of the Greek-Greek 
Cypriot joint defense doctrine. 

</TEXT>

