<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Kliridhis Reiterates Goodwill in Negotiations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1601113694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1000 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1601113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Glavkos Kliridhis has said that our 
side will continue to show goodwill in negotiations for a just, 
viable, and functional Cyprus solution. He warned, however, 
that it would be wrong to misinterpret the goodwill as a 
willingness to accept a solution that will not secure the 
withdrawal of the occupation troops and the implementation of 
human rights and basic freedoms. Kliridhis was speaking at 
ceremony to unveil a statue of Griyorios Avxendiou dedicated by 
Lisi Municipality in Kalo Khorion, Larnaca. 
  Kliridhis reiterated that the struggle continues to free 
Cyprus from the occupation troops and settlers, to secure the 
right to return of the refugees, to safeguard human rights for 
all citizens, and to determine the fate of the missing persons. 
He added that we are also striving for Cyprus to join the 
European Union and to achieve progress in conditions of 
permanent peace and security. He stressed: We will accept 
nothing less than this. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

