<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportedly Discontent With Political Parties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701084694 Nicosia O AGON in Greek 17 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC1701084694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia O AGON </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Kostakis Andoniou] </F>
  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis has privately expressed 
his strong discontent with the absoluteness that characterizes 
the stance of certain political parties on the issue of 
confidence-building measures. Specifically, President Kliridhis 
stresses: The stance of these political parties makes his 
handling of policy more difficult and does not allow him to 
develop easily the policy he has in mind, especially in view of 
the expected acceptance of the confidence-building measures by 
the Turkish side and the beginning of talks. 
  Political circles have characteristically said the message 
these parties have sent to the world creates a negative 
impression of the Greek Cypriot side's sincerity about the 
negotiations; and on the other hand, it gives the Turkish side 
material for propaganda. 
  In light of the above, and despite the fact that he accepts 
the right of these parties to express their positions as they 
believe appropriate, President Kliridhis feels that their 
behavior makes it difficult for him to develop his policy on the 
issue of the confidence-building measures. 

</TEXT>

