<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament President Criticizes Greek Government Actions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1501091594 Nicosia ALITHIA in Greek 15 Jan 94 pp 1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC1501091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia ALITHIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] House of Representatives President Alexis Galanos 
strongly attacked Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou's 
government from the parliament's official podium. Galanos 
accused the Papandreou government of impolitic actions and lack 
of sensitivity toward the government and people of Cyprus. 
  Despite his efforts to maintain diplomatic protocol, Galanos 
did not refrain from using very strong language to describe the 
way the Greek government action in canceling the Cypriot 
National Council meeting with the prime minister in Athens and 
for recalling National Guard Commander Lieutenant General 
Yeoryios Siradhakis. 
  "I would like to express my personal discontent with the 
fact 
that the Papandreou government, which raised the morale of our 
people by elevating the Cyprus issue as a national priority, did 
not show the necessary sensitivity toward our government and 
people in these two cases, which were, at the least, 
unfortunate," said Galanos in his address during the debate on 
the 1994 state budgets. Galanos explained that the two 
incidents to which he referred include the last minute 
cancellation of the National Council's visit to Greece and the 
impolitic firing of Lt. Gen. Siradhakis, especially considering 
the way it was done, despite the Greek prime minister's 
assurances and commitment to President Glavkos Kliridhis. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

