<H3> <TI>   House of Representatives Approves 1994 State Budgets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701202494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1848 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1701202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The House of Representatives approved the 1994 
state budgets by a majority vote. DISI [Democratic Rally], AKEL 
[Restorative Party of the Working People], DIKO [Democratic 
Party], and Liberals Party Chairman Nikolaos Rolandhis voted for 
the budgets. Socialist Party EDEK [United Democratic Union of 
Cyprus] voted against them, except for the Refugee-Relief Fund 
allocations. 
  The budgets project 1.043 billion pounds in expenditures, 
843 
million pounds in revenue, and a 200-million pound deficit. 
[passage omitted] 
  Out of the 47 deputies present, 42 voted for the budgets and 
five voted against. 

</TEXT>

