<F P=100> SWITZERLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   France Warned over Failure To Extradite Iranians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301113494 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 1110 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1301113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Swiss Government says it is considering further 
steps in connection with France's refusal to extradite two 
Iranians wanted in Switzerland. The Swiss Foreign Ministry made 
the announcement without providing details, but an investigating 
judge says he is continuing enquiries, hoping for new 
developments in the affair. 
  France reneged on previous extradition pledges and expelled 
the two wanted men last year. The expulsion caused a diplomatic 
row between France and Switzerland and the Swiss justice 
minister, Arnold Koller, said on Wednesday that Switzerland 
would raise the subject with the Council of Europe, if 
necessary. He said France should explain why the Iranians were 
not extradited as originally agreed. The two Iranians are 
wanted in connection with the killing of an Iranian opposition 
leader, Kazem Rajavi, in Geneva nearly three years [as heard] 
ago. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

