<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Arrest Drug Smugglers; Escapee From U.S. Jail </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401193494 Paris AFP in English 1911 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1401193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Genoa, Italy, Jan 14 (AFP) -- Police Friday [14 
January] said they had arrested 23 Italians, including one who 
made a spectacular break from a U.S. jail, on suspicion of 
running heroin from Turkey and cocaine from Colombia. 
  They were said to be part of a 70-strong gang linked to the 
Mafia in southern Italy and Colombia's Medellin Cartel. 
  Among those arrested was Sicilian Umberto Pitino, 49, who 
was 
detained in 1991 when authorities smashed the so-called pizza 
connection in the United States. He escaped by helicopter from 
Raleigh jail in North Carolina with the aid of a Colombian drug 
producer. 
  Police said cocaine totalling 20 kilos (44 pounds) had been 
smuggled from Colombia aboard a ship hidden in musical 
instruments or navigational apparatus. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

