<H3> <TI>   Juppe Comments on `Odious' Killing of French Citizen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601193994 Paris Radio France International in French 1830 
GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Let us now listen to the reaction of the French 
foreign minister to the killing. Alain Juppe spoke to Farida 
Ayari a few minutes ago, as soon as he arrived in South Africa: 
  [Begin recording] [Juppe, in progress] ...my outrage at this 
odious killing. We immediately took the necessary steps with 
the Algerian authorities. Our ambassador has been received by 
Prime Minister Redha Malek. As you know, we had taken 
significant security measures, but of course, because the French 
community in Algeria is so scattered, no security system is 50 
percent efficient, or even 40 percent, as I said earlier. 
Unfortunately, this was proven true the hard way. 
  [Ayari] Will you be taking other steps? 
  [Juppe] Of course. In particular we are going to try to find 
out how we can reduce the number of staff at our official 
facilities, so that civil servants are exposed as little as 
possible. [end recording] 
  Asked whether France would close its consulate in Algeria, 
Alain Juppe answered, I quote, we have not reached that stage 
yet. 

</TEXT>

